name: ROYAL AERO CLUB OF NSW INCORPORATED
about: The Royal Aero Club of New South Wales, founded in 1920 by courageous aviators of the Australian Flying Corps, is one of the largest and most vibrant flying clubs in the Commonwealth. With a rich aviation heritage, we offer comprehensive flight training for hobbyists and career pilots, leading to various qualifications. Our scenic flights provide unforgettable experiences over breathtaking scenery. As a not-for-profit, volunteer-run Part 141 Flight Training Organisation, we prioritize safety and excellence, having trained over 400 pilots in our early years and continuing to shape the next generation of aviators with great enthusiasm. Join us to put wings on your dreams.
services:
["Trial Introductory Flights (TIF)
Recreational Pilot Licence (RPL)
Private Pilot Licence (PPL)
Commercial Pilot Licence (CPL)
Night VFR Rating (NVFR)
Flying Training Camp 2025"]
